{
  "texts": [
    "The second part consisted of five statements aimed at collecting demographic (S1), educational (S2), and professional (S3) data.",
    "Statements four and five (S4 and S5) were designed to explore involvement in Decentralized Autonomous Organizations (DAOs), focusing primarily on Decentralized Science (DeSci).",
    "Statement four was designed to quantify the number of DAOs in which participants held membership, whereas statement five aimed to assess the duration of such involvement.",
    "Criteria for DAO membership relevant to S4 and S5 were explicitly defined: participants had attended at least one community meeting in the past 3 months or had to own one or more governance tokens, including Non-Fungible Tokens (NFTs), of a DeSci-DAO.",
    "A comprehensive distribution of the responses, represented as percentages of the total participant pool, is shown in Table 9."
  ]
}